-- Tampa Bay Rays Hire Ex-Yankees Pitching Coach Eiland as Special Assistant
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2010-12-22T18:08:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/tampa-bay-rays-hire-ex-yankees-pitching-coach-eiland-as-special-assistant.html
The Tampa Bay Rays hired former New
York Yankees pitching coach Dave Eiland as a special assistant
and scout, the team said in a statement.  Eiland, 44, was in charge of New York’s pitching staff for
three seasons. In 2010, the Yankees’ 4.06 earned run average was
15th among Major League Baseball’s 30 franchises.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  